    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "# Loading the dataset\n",
    "data = pd.read_csv('retail_sales_dataset.csv') \n",
    "df.head()\n",
    "# Step 1: Data Cleaning\n",
    "# Check for missing values\n",
    "print(\"Missing Values:\\n\", data.isnull().sum())\n",
    "\n",
    "# Fill missing numerical values with mean\n",
    "numerical_columns = ['Age', 'Quantity', 'Price per Unit', 'Total Amount']\n",
    "for col in numerical_columns:\n",
    "    if col in data.columns:\n",
    "        data[col].fillna(data[col].mean(), inplace=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Remove duplicates\n",
    "data.drop_duplicates(inplace=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Step 2: Descriptive Statistics\n",
    "print(\"\\nDescriptive Statistics:\\n\", data[numerical_columns].describe())\n",
    "\n",
    "# Categorical column modes\n",
    "print(\"\\nMost Common Gender:\", data['Gender'].mode()[0])\n",
    "print(\"Most Common Product Category:\", data['Product Category'].mode()[0])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Step 3: Time Series Analysis\n",
    "data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'])  # Ensure Date is in datetime format\n",
    "data.set_index('Date', inplace=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ploting sales trends over time\n",
    "data['Total Amount'].resample('M').sum().plot(title='Monthly Sales Trend', figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Month')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Total Sales')\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Step 4: Customer and Product Analysis\n",
    "# Top-performing products\n",
    "top_products = data.groupby('Product Category')['Total Amount'].sum().sort_values(ascending=False)\n",
    "print(\"\\nTop-Performing Products:\\n\", top_products)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Customer age distribution\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))\n",
    "sns.histplot(data['Age'], bins=15, kde=True)\n",
    "plt.title('Customer Age Distribution')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Age')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Frequency')\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Step 5: Correlation Heatmap\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))\n",
    "sns.heatmap(data[numerical_columns].corr(), annot=True, cmap='coolwarm')\n",
    "plt.title('Correlation Heatmap')\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Step 6: Visualization of Product Categories\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "sns.barplot(x=top_products.index, y=top_products.values)\n",
    "plt.xticks(rotation=45)\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Step 7: Insights and Recommendations\n",
    "print(\"\\nInsights and Recommendations:\")\n",
    "print(\"- Focus on the top-performing product categories to maximize revenue.\")\n",
    "print(\"- Tailor marketing efforts to the age group with the highest frequency.\")\n",
    "print(\"- Use time-series trends to plan promotional campaigns during peak months.\")"
   ]
